    dc:creator "Balete, Danilo S.; Heaney, Lawrence R.; Rickart, Eric A.; Quidlat, Roselyn S.; Rowsey, Dakota M.; Olson, Link E." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A re-assessment of diversity among Philippine gymnures (Mammalia: Erinaceidae Podogymnura), with a new species from eastern Mindanao" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532502>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532474>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532488>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532492> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532502>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Dorsal (A), ventral (B) and lateral (C) views of the skull and lateral view of the mandible (D) of Podogymnura intermedia (FMNH 186805, holotype); scale bar refers to these images. E, occlusal view of the second mandibular molar of Podogymnura intermedia holotype; arrow points to a small cusp at the base of talonid, between the entoconid and metaconid." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7532502/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532474>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of Mindanao and adjacent islands showing some major topographic features; mountains where Podogymnura truei (Mt.Apo), P. minima (Mt. Kitanglad Range), P. aureospinula (Bucas Grande and Dinagat Islands), and P. intermedia n. sp. (Mt. Hamiguitan and Mt. Kampalili) occur, and other important peaks, are shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7532474/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532488>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Photographs of skulls of Podogymnura intermedia (holotype, FMNH 186805, A-D), P. truei (FMNH 56169, E-H), and P. minima (FMNH 146594; I-L). All skulls approximately life size." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7532488/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7532492>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. A. Bivariate plot of condylo-incisive length (CIL) and breadth of braincase (BBC) measurements comparing Podogymnura truei, P. minima, and P. intermedia n. sp. B. Results from the Principal Component Analysis of four small species of Podogymnura (excluding P. aureospinula) based on 15 cranial, dental, and mandibular measurements (see text)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7532492/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

